name: Caio Sato after AfterSherrieLevine.com
description: In 1936 Walker Evans photographed the Burroughs, a family of sharecroppers in Depression era Alabama. In 1979 in Sherrie Levine rephotographed Walker Evans' photographs from the exhibition catalog "First and Last." In 2001 Michael Mandiberg scanned these same photographs, and created AfterSherrieLevine.com. Now the ultra cool contemporary artist Caio Sato downloaded it and minted to give it life again.
